               <Description>function does not verify that its argument is the proper type, leading to arbitrary memory write</Description>
               <Link>https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2007-1376</Link>
            </Observed_Example>
            <Observed_Example>
               <Reference>CVE-2007-1220</Reference>
               <Description>invalid syscall arguments bypass code execution limits</Description>
               <Link>https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2007-1220</Link>
            </Observed_Example>
            <Observed_Example>
